Terminal Countdown Timer

The [prgm]termdown[/prgm] command displays a countdown timer in the terminal.

$ [prgm]termdown[/prgm] [arg-value]5m[/arg-value]              # Countdown from 5 minutes
$ [prgm]termdown[/prgm] [arg-value]10[/arg-value]              # Countdown from 10 seconds

[bold]Output effects[/bold]

$ [prgm]termdown[/prgm] [arg-value]25m[/arg-value] [arg]--blink[/arg]     # Blink terminal when complete
$ [prgm]termdown[/prgm] [arg-value]30m[/arg-value] [arg]--exec[/arg] [arg-value]"notify-send 'Timer done!'"[/arg-value]  # Execute command when complete

[dim]Press Ctrl+C to cancel the countdown. Supports time formats: s (seconds), m (minutes), h (hours).[/dim]
